cs.SI, cs.GT, cs.CY, cs.DC, cs.NI 

This paper is about incentivizing participatory sensing, which involves collecting data from a large number of users. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses game theory to derive optimal service demands, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper addresses practical considerations and uses stochastic programming, which could place it in categories such as cs.CY (Computational Geometry), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
